== Noun ==
holmberry
  1. a holly [http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/holly holly] bush. Used as an adjective in Thomas Hardy's [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thomas_Hardy Thomas Hardy] "Tess of the d'Urbervilles" [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tess_of_the_d'Urbervilles "Tess of the d'Ubervilles"]. ''"Let me put one little kiss on those holmberry lips, Tess, or even on that warmed cheek, and I'll stop - on my honour, I will!"'' Could be a derivative [http://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/derivative derivative] of "holm tree" - evergreen oak of Southern Europe [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Southern_Europe Southern Europe] having leaves somewhat resembling those of holly
